TERMINOLOGY

 - Adam
      : new (totally random) critter

 - Adam Distance (ad)
      : generations with mutations since adam


STARTUP OPTIONS                                                                                                                                                                              

  option         [default value]

  Global Settings
  --worldsize               [10]  Creates a 10x10 world
  --energy                 [100]  Energy in the system: 100*food_energy(2500) = 250000
  --mincritters             [10]  If less than 10 critters are present, insert an adam
  --retinasperrow           [20]  Place 20 retinas on a row (bottom left of window)   

  Critter Settings
  --critter_maxlifetime   [1200]  Max amount of frames a critter can live
  --critter_maxenergy     [5000]  Max amount of energy in a critter      
  --critter_startenergy   [2500]  Starting amount of energy for a new critter
  --critter_maxchildren    [100]  Max amount of children a critter can spawn 
  --critter_maxbullets     [200]  Max amount of bullets a critter can fire   
  --critter_minenergyproc [3000]  Min amount of energy required for procreation
  --critter_minenergyfire    [1]  Min amount of energy required for firing a bullet
  --critter_size            [10]  Size of a critter                                
  --critter_speed           [50]  Critter speed                                    
  --critter_sightrange      [30]  Distance a critter can see (30 = 3 floor squares)
  --critter_retinasize       [7]  Resolution of critter's retina: 7x7
  --critter_colorneurons     [3]  Earch color of every pixel (RGBA) will get [3] neurons (only for new adams)
  --critter_mutationrate    [10]  When a critter procreates there is a 10% chance it will mutate
  --critter_maxmutations    [10]  When a critter mutates, it can do 10 mutations at maximum
  --critter_flipnewborns          If set, newborns will be flipped 180 degrees

  Food Settings
  --food_maxlifetime       [400]  Maximum amount of frames food can live
  --food_maxenergy        [2500]  Maximum amount of energy in a food unit
  --food_size               [15]  Size of a food unit

  Brain Settings
  --brain_maxneurons                           [1000]  Max neurons per critter
  --brain_minsynapses                             [1]  Min synapses per neuron
  --brain_maxsynapses                           [100]  Max synapses per neuron
  --brain_minneuronsatbuildtime                  [20]  Min neurons for a new critter
  --brain_maxneuronsatbuildtime                  [30]  Max neurons for a new critter
  --brain_minsynapsesatbuildtime                  [1]  Min synapses when creating new neuron
    --brain_mutate_minsynapsesatbuildtime              If set, the value above will mutate
  --brain_maxsynapsesatbuildtime                 [60]  Max synapses when creating new neuron
    --brain_mutate_maxsynapsesatbuildtime              If set, the value above will mutate
  --brain_percentchanceinhibitoryneuron          [50]  % chance neuron is inhibitory (vs exhibitory)
    --brain_mutate_percentchanceinhibitoryneuron       If set, the value above will mutate
  --brain_percentchancemotorneuron               [50]  % chance a neuron is a motor neuron, this value seems
                                                       high, but when it tries to create a motor neuron that is
                                                       is already taken, it will stay a normal neuron
    --brain_mutate_percentchancemotorneuron            If set, the value above will mutate
  --brain_percentchanceplasticneuron             [20]  % chance a neuron applies synaptic plasticity
    --brain_mutate_percentchanceplasticneuron          If set, the value above will mutate
  --brain_minplasticitystrengthen               [100]  Min weight by which plastic synapses strengthen (1/100)
  --brain_maxplasticitystrengthen              [1000]  Max weight by which plastic synapses strengthen (1/1000)
  --brain_minplasticityweaken                  [1000]  Min weight by which plastic synapses weaken (1/1000)
  --brain_maxplasticityweaken                 [10000]  Max weight by which plastic synapses weaken (1/10000)
    --brain_mutate_plasticityfactors                   If set, all values above will mutate
  --brain_minfiringthreshold                      [2]  Min firing threshold of a neuron
    --brain_mutate_minfiringthreshold                  If set, the value above will mutate
  --brain_maxfiringthreshold                     [10]  Max firing threshold of a neuron
    --brain_mutate_maxfiringthreshold                  If set, the value above will mutate
  --brain_maxdendridicbranches                    [3]  Max dendridic branches per neuron
    --brain_mutate_maxdendridicbranches                If set, the value above will mutate
  --brain_percentchanceconsistentsynapses        [50]  % chance neuron has consistent synapses
                                                       meaning all (new) synapses are inhibitory or exhibitory
    --brain_mutate_percentchanceconsistentsynapses     If set, the value above will mutate
  --brain_percentchanceinhibitorysynapses        [50]  % chance a synapse is inhibitory (vs exhibitory)
    --brain_mutate_percentchanceinhibitorysynapses     If set, the value above will mutate
  --brain_percentchancesensorysynapse            [20]  % chance a synapse connects with a sensor (inputneuron)
    --brain_mutate_percentchancesensorysynapse         If set, the value above will mutate
  --brain_percentmutateeffectaddneuron           [10]  % chance of adding a neuron for a mutationrun
  --brain_percentmutateeffectremoveneuron        [10]  % chance of removing a neuron for a mutationrun
  --brain_percentmutateeffectalterneuron         [20]  % chance of altering a neuron for a mutationrun
  --brain_percentmutateeffectaddsynapse          [30]  % chance of adding a synapse for a mutationrun
  --brain_percentmutateeffectremovesynapse       [30]  % chance of removing a synapse for a mutationrun
    --brain_mutate_mutateeffects                       If set, all values above will mutate

BUTTONS

Engine / World Operations
  F1            : print settings and toggle pause program
  F2            : show fps (10 frames average)           

  F3            : decrease Minimum Critters
  F4            : increase Minimum Critters

  F5            : decrease energy in the system by the energy amount of 25 food
  F6            : increase energy in the system by the energy amount of 25 food

  F7            : insert new critter (adam)

  F8            : toggle Timed Food Inserts
                  inserts 100 food every 3 generations, driving the population up and down.

  F9            : decrease max mutations per mutant
  F10           : increase max mutations per mutant

  F11           : decrease mutation rate (%)
  F12           : increase mutation rate (%)

  Insert        : toggle hide critter retinas.

  w             : create a horizontal wall
  x             : destroy the wall        
  c             : toggle gate in wall center

  f             : toggle follow the youngest critter untill it dies.

  Page Up       : load all critters from "~/.critterding/load" directory
  Page Down     : save all critters into "~/.critterding/save/(timestamp)" directory

  keypad -      : decrease energy in the system by the energy amount of 1 food
  keypad +      : increase energy in the system by the energy amount of 1 food

Camera Operations
  Arrow Up      : move forward
  Arrow Down    : move backward
  Arrow Left    : strafe left  
  Arrow Right   : strafe right 
  Home          : move up      
  End           : move down    
  NumKey 2      : look up      
  NumKey 8      : look down    
  NumKey 4      : look left    
  NumKey 6      : look right   


OTHER THINGS

 - Make sure the retina boxes in the lower left of the window never leave the
   boundaries of the window.  Offscreen rendering is not supported by almost any
   video card drivers.  For some drivers you are not even allowed to minimize the window or
   change desktops.  You should notice a big dropoff in population when this occurs.

 - Slow videocards will gain some performance gains by making the window's width smaller.
   Again watch out the retinas do not leave the window boundaries, the option --retinasperrow
   can be used to level your needs.

 - Hiding the retinas is (slightly) more costly than leaving them on.


